The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, spoke at the Federalist Society's Seventh Annual Executive Branch Review Conference. He praised the organization for its commitment to the principles of limited government and the Constitution, and thanked them for their support of the Trump administration. Pence highlighted the administration's achievements in cutting federal regulations and appointing conservative judges to the federal courts. He also expressed concern about the increasing use of nationwide injunctions by district court judges, calling for the Supreme Court to clarify the limits of their power. Pence emphasized the importance of freedom and free markets, and warned against the dangers of socialism. He urged members of the Federalist Society to continue promoting conservative principles and fighting for the agenda of the Trump administration. Pence ended his speech by quoting the words inscribed on the Liberty Bell and calling on the audience to win the next generation by explaining the principles of the nation's founding.